Reducing the consumption of highly processed foods is very useful for your heart. Currently, up to 35% of the average Australian diet consists of highly processed foods, such as:


Baked goods cakes, cookies and pastries;

chocolate;

Potato chips;

lollipop;

Sugary drinks, soft drinks, energy drinks, sports drinks;

Take away food such as pizza burgers.


These foods are usually rich in sugar, salt, saturated fat and trans fat, so they are not a heart-healthy diet. Try to eat these foods only occasionally in small amounts.
